(secondQuint)Assessment of Safety and Effectiveness of Biodegradable Temporizing Matrix in the Treatment of Deep Burn Skin Injuries.

 This is a multi-center, single arm, traditional feasibility study to allow a preliminary assessment of the safety and effectiveness of BTM treatment.

 Patients with 10-70% TBSA burns will have BTM devices implanted in areas with deep partial or full thickness burns to treat at least 5% TBSA.

